      "subpart_at_time": "Powerplant",
      "title_at_amendment": "Fuel system lightning protection.",
      "text": "[The fuel system must be designed and arranged to prevent the ignition of fuel vapor within the system by-- (a) Direct lightning strikes to area having a high probability of stroke attachment: (b) Swept lightning strokes on area where swept strokes are highly probable; and (c) Corona or streamering at fuel vent outlets.]",
